{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require a named minister to respond to petitions with over 10,000 signatures",
        "additional_details": "There are currently 140 petitions which have had a government response. Many of the responses reject the petition, and we think they more or less say nothing at all. We think having a relevant minister tie their name and reputation to a response would help them to consider it an action for campaign, and not to simply reject it.            \r\n",
        "background": "Require a relevant minister to attach their name to the response to every petition, with a response that explains why it can or cannot happen. Responses should not just state that the government has no plans to accept the request of the petition.\r\n",
